  /* Section 9: Conclusioni */
  'arg.s9.label': 'Section 9',
  'arg.s9.title': 'Conclusions and outlook',
  'arg.s9.p1': "In the first two years, the Milei government produced significant and documented macroeconomic results. Disinflation is the most robust: monthly inflation had not fallen below 3% since August 2021. The primary fiscal surplus is real, but largely cyclical — dependent on spending cuts and inflationary erosion, not on structural revenue expansion.",
  'arg.s9.p2': "The program's sustainability depends on the capacity to transform stabilization into real growth. Without expansion of the tax base, spending cuts reach a political and social limit beyond which further reductions are not feasible. A reversal of the fiscal surplus would re-open pressure on monetary issuance, reactivating the deficit-monetization-inflation spiral documented in the pre-Milei period.",
  'arg.s9.p3': "Stabilization is real, but growth is not built on cuts alone. The Milei program has broken a vicious cycle; it remains to be demonstrated that it can initiate a virtuous one. The variables to monitor in the coming months will determine whether Argentina is building a structural foundation or consuming the political capital of an exceptional phase.",

